FBIS4-59401 "drnes093_o_94002" FBIS-NES-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 SYRIA Yemeni Envoy Arrives With Letter From al-Bid Yemeni Envoy Arrives With Letter From al-Bid Meets With al-Asad JN1205183794 Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network in Arabic 1805 GMT 12 May 94 JN1205183794 Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network Arabic BFN [Text] At 1830 today, President Hafiz al-Asad received Salih Abu-Bakr Bin-Husaynun, Yemeni minister of oil and mineral wealth. The meeting was attended by Faruq al-Shar', foreign minister; Dr. Nadir Nabulsi, minister of oil and and mineral resources; and 'Abduh Shatfah, the Yemeni ambassador in Damascus. Bin-Husaynun conveyed to his excellency the president a message from Yemeni Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid. Discussions dealt with the situation in Yemen. His excellency the president stressed Syria's extreme interest in the ongoing events in the Yemeni arena. He reiterated the call for the Yemeni brothers to resolve their differences through dialogue, away from fighting, with a spirit of brotherhood, and with a view to safeguarding the homeland's unity and the safety of its children.
